                <h2>My Music Journey</h2>
                <p>
                    Unlike most musicians I know, I got into music later at the age of 12. 
                    I used to practice a piano app on my phone to learn songs to then take forward to my music lessons 
                    at school. I learned little simple tunes such as happy birthday and jingle bells.
                    1 year later, I was fortunate enough to be able to have private piano lessons, where I would spend the rest 
                    of highschool progressing at a fast rate through the grades of piano and keep up and be on top of my exams. 
                    I had fun playing piano and I enjoyed teaching and passing on my knowledge to others, so when choosing a profession 
                    to pursue for the rest of my life, I've chosen teaching music. I worked towards my applications to universitys and getting 
                    good grades on my exams. 
                    Now I am here at the University of Aberdeen and am working towards my dream to teach music.
                </p>
